    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="343"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/1024</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1915</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>698. Your 665, 25th.<note n="2" xml:id="d343fn2">See footnote 1.</note> Foreign
                    Office states that the Allied Governments consider German laws and publications
                    as one of the most efficacious means of propaganda against the interests of
                    their national defense and that under these circumstances the Government of the
                    Republic regrets it cannot undertake to exempt books and publications destined
                    to American public library from the measures of decree of March 13.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
